INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Getting started with Configurator', 'getting-started-with-configurator', '', '<p>It looks like this is the first time you are running Configurator, so we thought youd like a couple of pointers on using the system. In case you dont already know, Configurator is our Template Management System (T.M.S.) and is used to control most aspects of Morph.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/maskot-right.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0"> We have poured our hearts into both Morph &amp; Configuratort hope you enjoy using it as much as we did making it!</p>\r\n<p>Take a couple of minutes to go through the different help sections and once you feel ready to jump in, simply close this window and get started.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This help pane can be easily accessed at any time,</strong> either by clicking on the Getting Started button in the top shelf, or using on of the built in keyboard shortcuts (cmd + h).</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:36:22', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:35:27', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:36:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 2, '', '', 2, 7, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Working in fullscreen mode', 'working-in-fullscreen-mode', '', '<p>We all know how having that extra bit of real estate can really help your productivity, so we decided to add a feature to Configurator to allow you to easily toggle between fullscreen mode and normal mode.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<h4>Clicking the fullscreen link in the top shelf:</h4>\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-fullscreen-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0">There are two ways that you can use this feature. The first is by using the "Fullscreen mode" link in the top shelf (see the pic below), which </p>\r\n<h4>Using the built in shortcuts:</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The other (and easier) way is to use the built in keyboard shortcuts. If you are on a mac, simply pressing <strong>cmd + f</strong> to toggle between the two views. All other users (windows, linux, etc) can use <strong>ctrl + f</strong>.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:36:55', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:35:34', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:36:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 3, '', '', 2, 3, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Automatic update notifications', 'automatic-update-notifications', '', '<p>One of the challenges when developing Configurator, was to make it super easy for our members to know when new versions are available. The result is our built in notification system.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-updates-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0"></p>\r\n<p>Simply keep an eye on the top shelf to be notified when new versions of Morph, Configurator or your current themelet are available.</p>\r\n<p>Column 1 (green) is your installed version, column 2 (red) is the latest available version and the tick or cross icon in column 3 (blue) indicates whether your installed version is up-to-date.</p>\r\n<p>If your installed version and the online version differ, the second version will be hyperlinked to the JoomlaJunkie downloads, allowing you to go and get the latest version.</p>\r\n<p>We are currently investing an option to allow you to automatically upgrade from within Configurator, but more on that later ;)</p>\r\n<h4>Morph &amp; Configurator updates on Twitter</h4>\r\n<p>We have also setup a dedicated Twitter account for Morph related updates &amp; news. We highly recommend that you follow <a href="http://twitter.com/jMorph" target="_blank">@jMorph</a> to get the latest themelet releases, updates and more!</p>\r\n<h4>Subscribe to our bi-monthly newsletter</h4>\r\n<p>Last but not least, if you aren''t already subscribed to our newsletter, you can do so by <a href="" target="_blank">following this link</a>.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:37:35', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:35:39', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:37:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 4, '', '', 2, 1, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Working with your sites assets', 'working-with-your-sites-assets', '', '<p>The terms "assets" refers to the digital media that is specific to your project, such as your sites custom backgrounds, logos and themelets, etc. The assets tab allows you to manage these without having to use an ftp client.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-assets-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0">The assets folder currently only consists of your custom backgrounds, logos and themelets. We plan on extending this to include various different types of backups as well as different graphic "packs".</p>\r\n<p>The reason why they are stored together is so that they can be stored outside your templates folder, allowing you to upgrade Morph without overriding your custom images, themelets, etc.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:38:03', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:35:44', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:38:03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 5, '', '', 2, 1, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Understanding Morphs methods of control', 'understanding-morphs-methods-of-control', '', '<p>If you use the analogy of Morph as a sports car, the engine would be the core framework, the themelet would be the design/body of the car &amp; the dashboard would be Morph''s Configurator.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-methods-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0">In order to have total control, even at high speeds, the driver has a wide variety of methods he can use to control this powerful machine, to do exactly what is desired. A comprehensive dashboard as well as the various controls such as the steering, pedals, gears etc make up the various methods of control that are needed.</p>\r\n<p>Morph''s other primary Method of Control is its FX Range, namely: PageFX, MenuFx, ModuleFX &amp; ContentFX. These are stemmed from Joomla''s "suffix" feature. Which in its simplest form is a way of appending a custom class to a page, module or menu.</p>\r\n<p>Using a combination of different page or module suffixes, not only are you able to transform your sites layout on a page-by-page basis, but also mix &amp; match your own custom module styles.</p>\r\n<p>We highly recommend that you checkout the relevant quick start guides in order to get the most out of the FX Range of features.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:38:56', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:35:50', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:38:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 6, '', '', 2, 1, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Quick start guides to get you going', 'quick-start-guides-to-get-you-going', '', '<p>The Quick Start Guides are the quickest way for you to take advantage of Morphs FX Range and are close at hand in Configurators top shelf.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-guides-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0"> The PageFX guide lists all the <strong>page suffixes</strong> that you can use to change your sites layouts on a page by page basis.</p>\r\n<p>The MenuFX guide lists the suffixes that are used to activate the various menu options built into Morph.</p>\r\n<p>The ModuleFX guide lists the various module heading, background &amp; icon styles that you have at your disposal.</p>\r\n<p>The Block &amp; Position Maps give you a visual representation of Morph''s building blocks &amp; the various module positions that are available. </p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:39:38', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:35:55', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:39:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 7, '', '', 2, 1, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Inline contextual help is close at hand', 'inline-contextual-help-is-close-at-hand', '', '<p>We realize that when getting started with Morph &amp; Configurator &amp; some of the options may not make immediate sense, so we have added extensive contextual help to assist you every step of the way!</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-contextual-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0">Every single option in Configurator has either an info or help icon next to it.</p>\r\n<p>The <strong>info icon</strong> indicates that there is a standard tooltip available. These are generally for options which are more common and easier to understand.</p>\r\n<p>The <strong>help icon</strong> indicates that there is an pop-up help page available. These are used when a simple info tooltip just isn''t enough.</p>\r\n<p>Let us know using the feedback form if anything doesn''t make sense.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:41:07', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:36:00', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:41:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 6, 0, 8, '', '', 2, 1, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Using the built in keyboard shortcuts', 'using-the-built-in-keyboard-shortcuts', '', '<p>We all love keyboard shortcuts, as they often boost your productivity. With this in mind, we have added a number of different keyboard shortcuts to increase your productivity when using Configurator.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="../administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-shortcuts-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0"></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong> + S</strong> = Save your current settings</li>\r\n	<li><strong> + F</strong> = Toggle fullscreen mode</li>\r\n	<li><strong> + H</strong> = Open this help dialog</li>\r\n	<li><strong> + P</strong> = Open your preferences pane</li>\r\n	<li><strong> + V</strong> = Preview your site in a new window</li>\r\n</ul>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:41:43', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:36:05', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:41:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 6, 0, 9, '', '', 2, 1, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Setting your preferences', 'setting-your-preferences', '', '<p>The preferences pane can either by accessed from the link in the top shelf, or using the built in keyboard shortcut.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-feedback-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0"></p>\r\n<p>The preferences pane can either by accessed from the link in the top shelf, or using the built in keyboard shortcut.</p>\r\n<p>Mac users can use <strong>cmd + p</strong>, whereas users on all other systems can use <strong>ctrl + p</strong>.</p>			\r\n<h4>Preferences options:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Enable / disable keyboard shortcuts</li>\r\n	<li>Change the shelf position (top or bottom)</li>\r\n	<li>Re-activate tab intros</li>\r\n	<li>Disable updates notification</li>\r\n	<li>Enable / disable tips</li>\r\n</ul>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:42:13', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:36:11', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:42:13', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 7, 0, 10, '', '', 2, 0, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Submitting a bug or suggestion', 'submitting-a-bug-or-suggestion', '', '<p>We believe that submitting a bug or sending a suggestion should be super easy and NOT take you away from the interface you are providing feedback on.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-feedback-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0"> With that in mind we have built a really easy way for you to submit a bug or suggestion.</p>\r\n<p>You can either click on the <strong>Submit Feedback</strong> link in the top shelf, or use the built in keyboard shortcut.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mac users can use <strong>cmd + e</strong>, whereas users on all other systems can use <strong>ctrl + e</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Due to the vast number of users, we are not able to reply to emails that are received through Configurator. If you requires a response, please use the forum instead.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:44:18', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:36:19', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:44:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 5, 0, 11, '', '', 2, 0, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Extensive online documentation', 'extensive-online-documentation', '', '<p>We are working on extensive documentation and tutorials covering all aspects of both Morph &amp; Configurator. However...</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p><img src="administrator/components/com_configurator/images/splash-docs-bg.png" alt="maskot" align="right" border="0"></p>\r\n<p>Due to the fact that both Morph &amp; Configurator are still in changing daily, we have decided rather focus on the inline documentation within Configurator.</p>\r\n<p>We will be launching the dedicated Morph documentation site once Morph &amp; Configurator reach a stable release.</p>\r\n<p>We will also be adding a video tutorials section to Configurator once the layout is complete.</p>\r\n<p>Please use the inline documentation until the new documentation site is ready.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 10:44:47', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:36:26', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 10:44:47', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 6, 0, 12, '', '', 2, 0, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Understanding PageFX', 'understanding-pagefx', '', '<p>This is probably one of Morph''s most powerful features, this is because it gives users the ability to set a wide variety of layout combination''s on any specific pages or components on their website. With Morph you can easily switch the left sidebar from 200px to 300px wide in a matter of seconds without touching any code.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p>There are a total of "8 left sidebar" and "5 right sidebar" width (banner friendly) and position variations available. These options can be combined with each other to create literally dozens of layout combination''s on any page and each page can be different. As with all other features in the FX Range, its super easy to set a layout for a page, there is nothing to configure, its just a matter of adding the required suffix or combined suffixes to the page in Joomla!... as easy as that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PageFX not only sets the sidebar layouts, there are some other things you can do as well. With Configurator you can also set the main website width based on 4 preset options (750px, 950px, 974px and 100%).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lastly, developers can also make use of the Page Class Suffix feature to add a custom hook to any page or pages on a website. This "hook" is set at the highest level in the page structure, this means any visual css can now be added or over ridden for that page only. This can be used to Brand specific areas of site, color code different sections to match a color coded navigation, set gallery pages to have a dark content background or add styling for a specific season like Christmas without modifying the actual code in any way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gone are the days where developing for Joomla! means that the layout of the template you are using will dictate your content.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 6, '2009-07-11 12:01:16', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:38:55', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 12:01:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 1, '', '', 2, 0, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Understanding ModuleFX', 'understanding-modulefx', '', '<p>If you have ever used one of our (JoomlaJunkie) templates before, you may recognize this feature, it is in fact the popularity of this feature in our 1st generation templates that sparked the birth of the entire FX Range of features available in Morph.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p>A suffix by definition in grammar is "a suffix (also postfix, ending) is an affix which is placed after the stem of a word"  In the Joomla world, a suffix refers to text added to the modules code. Every module in Joomla has a parameter option (input box) to add a suffix. What this does is "affix" the suffix to the default css class of the module in the modules code. This can then be used to add additional styling to a module or give it a different look from other modules on the page using css..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ModuleFX in Morph, is the same as it was in our previous templates but its also a lot more advanced and usable than ever before, allowing users to literally modify the look of any module using a string of suffixes to combine dozens of background, header and icon styles to get create different front end appearances. Take a look at our <a href="http://modfx.joomlajunkie.com" target="_blank">ModuleFX Builder</a> that we created to help users of our 1st Generation templates build their module styles, this will give a good idea of how this feature works.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ModuleFX in Morph is a very long list of preset styles for the different elements of a module, ie. title or header and module container. More importantly most of these styles can be used in combination with each other to completely vary the effect. For example, a header icons can be applied with a heading color to create a module with a specific icon and color.... not fancy enough... what about adding the suffix or "rounded" and your module will automatically have round edges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is a list of the different types of styles that can be applied and combined together to get your website looking just how you want it without touching any of the code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Body Background</h3>\r\n<p>Set different background colors, images, gradients and other effects to any module.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Body font size and color</h3>\r\n<p>Set the module background font color and size.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Icons Styles</h3>\r\n<p>Apply different icons to the module headers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Heading background</h3>\r\n<p>Set different background colors, images, gradients to module headers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Module Heading text</h3>\r\n<p>Change the module headers font size, color and even transform the case of the letters.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Rounded</h3>\r\n<p>Convert your module with the above effects into a rounded corners module.</p>', 1, 1, 0, 5, '2009-07-11 12:05:19', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:38:23', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 12:05:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 1, '', '', 2, 0, 'robots=\nauthor=');
INSERT INTO `jos_content` VALUES('', 'Understanding Configurators role in Morph', 'understanding-configurators-role-in-morph', '', '<p>If Morph was a sports car, the dashboard would be Morph''s Configurator. This Joomla component puts you in the drivers seat with total control over this powerful machine, even at high speeds.</p>\r\n\r\n', '\r\n\r\n<p>If you use the analogy of "Morph as a sports car", for simplicity. The engine would be the core framework and the themelet would be the design or body of the car... the dashboard would be Morph''s Configurator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to have total control, even at high speeds, the driver has a wide variety of methods he can use to control this powerful machine, to do exactly what is desired. A comprehensive dashboard as well as the various controls such as the steering, pedals, gears etc make up the various methods of control that are needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a user of Morph, you have similar ways to control your site. Morph Configurator is one of two, methods of control in Morph, the other is the FX Range. Together these 2 methods give users the ability to manage literally every aspect of the front end interface of their site, with the utmost of ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lets start with Morph''s Configurator a Joomla component (see image on right), which puts you in the driving seat of your Joomla website by giving you finite control of a comprehensive set of options. Not only that, but this is all nicely wrapped up in a sleek interface that will certainly be seen as eye candy for those with a favor towards good design.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The options within Configurator, give you the ability to carry out many simple as well as complex tasks. From uploading and adding a new logo, heading colors, link colors, favicon, to controlling page layouts, converting blocks of content into various chromes and activating many enhancements like rounded corners etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you take Morph for a drive the first time, you will no doubt notice a plethora of powerful options available to you! Loads of attention to detail has been paid to the usability of this component with the aim to make it an experience users will not soon forget. There is also a vast amount of help, tips and inline documentation for each option and page, to coach you every step of the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Very importantly to developers, Morph has the ability to control and vastly change the position and type of content for each separate block that is output to the front end of the site. This gives developers the ability to easily adapt Morph to work with nearly any layout they need. This makes porting html web sites or designs to Joomla even easier and faster than ever before. (massive benefit of morph)</p>', 1, 1, 0, 7, '2009-07-11 12:15:13', 62, 'Morph', '2009-07-12 06:35:21', 62, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-07-11 12:15:13', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 4, 0, 1, '', '', 2, 1, 'robots=\nauthor=');
